FW IMPORTANTWorkstation Audits for move to ECSAll Move time is fast approaching IT will be performing a workstation audit on everyone who will be moving to ECS This audit is a physical audit of all your IT equipment computer telephone printers etc to document the equipment for each individual They will not be accessing the workstation in any way nor will we power off any workstation IT will begin the workstation audit Wednesday October th around pm and will continue for up to consecutive nights andor this weekend to ensure that we identify all equipment They will perform these audits after hours so as not to interrupt any daily activities Additionally with the Churn Freeze already in place it is important to note that once the audits are performed this week the information gathered is what will be used to plan for the migration of your IT equipment to ECS If changes are made to ANY of the workstations increase in monitors CPU upgrades laptop change etc these will not be captured and we cannot guarantee these changes will be in place with your move to ECS Please feel free to call me if you have any questions Heather Choate office mobile

Move Information for the th floorPST I just wanted to keep you posted on the information that I know so far abou t the move Of course it could change with in the next five minutes so it s not written in stone As of now the move for the th floor is scheduled for Friday Not exactly sure what time this is going to take place yet Please make sure that everyone is packed and ready by early Friday morning If there is so meone out on Friday please make sure they pack before they leave or you ha ve someone pack their stuff for them Please make sure that everyone clean s out their desk completely I know that boxes are hard to find right now If any of you know that you will need quite a few boxes for your groups please let me know ASAP so I can have them delivered by Thursday I know that there are some boxes on floor in the South building so you might wa nt to just go grab some Labels hopefully will be here Friday morning On ce I get them I will immediately pass them out I have attached the floor plan for the th floor for those of you that want to know where your group s are going if you dont know already Plus you might want to show it t o your groups so they know where to report to on Monday morning If you have any other questions please let me know I will update you as s oon as I find out more or if there are any changes to this schedule Thanks Sonia Hennessy Enron Networks Phone Fax Location EBg
